                            <comment id="52906" author="idotzang" created="Tue, 13 Apr 2010 01:21:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually, after testing further, making the field an instance field rather than static does not solve the problem - it appears as if Tomcat instantiates all listener objects before calling them.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;we ended up changing Log4jConfigListener to call shutdownLogging before initLogging, to clear the Log4j configuration.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Not sure if this is a Spring Security issue...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="53028" author="luke" created="Fri, 16 Apr 2010 02:15:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think this is essentially the same problem as reported in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-5977&quot; title=&quot;ContextLoader static logger causes early log4j initialization&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-5977&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-5977&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. I&apos;ve removed the logger field from HttpSessionEventPublisher. The logger reference is now obtained in each method before using it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
